<section class="py-3 py-lg-5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-6 mb-4">
                <div class="card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h1 class="text-center display-2 text-primary"><i class="icon-refresh" alt="Synchronization with Programs & Features"></i></h1>
                        <h3 class="text-center mb-0"><strong>Synchronization with Programs & Features</strong></h3>
                        <h3 class="text-center mb-3"><small>Ensure that your updates are consistent across all updates.</small></h3>
                        <p class="mb-0">
                            We often hear from customers that have manually updated an application or have some auto update feature enabled that sits outside of Chocolatey.
                            This can create complications when trying to ensure consistency between all updates of software and versions. Chocolatey for Business has solved this issue by enabling synchronization between programs and features.
                            This provides better integration with Windows so that you can quickly inspect what has changed and report correctly.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6 mb-4">
                <div class="card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h1 class="text-center display-2 text-primary"><i class="icon-rocket" alt="Streamline and Accelerate Deployments"></i></h1>
                        <h3 class="text-center mb-0"><strong>Streamline and Accelerate Deployments</strong></h3>
                        <h3 class="text-center mb-3"><small>Install Directory Override helping you minimize your effort and reduce errors.</small></h3>
                        <p class="mb-0">
                            Using native installers can be challenging when having to determine the native installer type (MSI, NSIS, InnoSetup, etc). Errors can also occur when passing incorrect instructions and arguments.
                            Chocolatey can simply override the default installation directory from a simple switch you pass to choco helping speed up your deployments and reducing errors.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6 mb-4">
                <div class="card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h1 class="text-center display-2 text-primary"><i class="icon-cogs" alt="Accessibility of Packages"></i></h1>
                        <h3 class="text-center mb-0"><strong>Accessibility of Packages</strong></h3>
                        <h3 class="text-center mb-3"><small>Create custom private repositories giving you access with no down time.</small></h3>
                        <p class="mb-0">
                            Internet reliability or changes to software updates can mean you don't always get the packages you need when you need them. Chocolatey allows you to build a dedicated repository within your IT environment.
                            This ensures that can build and run your updates from your dedicated Chocolatey repositories and also enable access to to other teams based on your internal policies.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6 mb-4">
                <div class="card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h1 class="text-center display-2 text-primary"><i class="icon-users" alt="Peace of Mind"></i></h1>
                        <h3 class="text-center mb-0"><strong>Peace of Mind</strong></h3>
                        <h3 class="text-center mb-3"><small>Prioritization of Bugs and Features backed with customer support.</small></h3>
                        <p class="mb-0">For our Chocolatey Business customers we offer expert help from our team of support engineers. Your subscription includes access to new releases, bug fixes, and knowledge base. You can also get support and advice from our ever growing community.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
                <div class="card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h1 class="text-center display-2 text-primary"><i class="icon-lock" alt="Secure & Validated"></i></h1>
                        <h3 class="text-center mb-0"><strong>Secure & Validated</strong></h3>
                        <h3 class="text-center mb-3"><small>Runtime Malware & Virus Protection minimizing risk.</small></h3>
                        <p>With the ongoing threat of viruses and malware it's important that you can trust the packages you access and run. Especially as you look to manage your Windows environment more securely.</p>
                        <p>We offer two options for our customers:</p>
                        <ol class="mb-0">
                            <li><strong>Managed Service:</strong> When Chocolatey downloads resources as part of a package install, Chocolatey for Business will automatically check the executables prior to running any content. If a certain number of positives have been identified (configurable), Chocolatey will fail the install automatically (can be overridden). Chocolatey partners with VirusTotal to offer this service.</li>
                            <li><strong>Integrated:</strong> If prefer to leverage your existing antivirus solution Chocolatey can be easily integrated with your current antivirus product.</li>
                        </ol>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>